Details: rank, N_c, n_C = F_3, F_4, F_5 (consecutive Fibonacci). g = L_4 (4th Lucas). n_C = rank + N_c is Fibonacci recurrence. Pell equation g^2 - n_C*N_c^2 = rank^2. Unique non-trivial 3-square rep of g^2. Both Pythagorean and modular select N_c=3.
